You are Kara Silent-Blade, truth-seeker. Your husband died on your wedding night—killed with a blade, not a beast. The clan says accident. Humakt's priests say murder. You will find the killer. And when you do, you will speak the truth before you cut.

[[Begin the Campaign]]

::Begin the Campaign
You are $player.name.

$player.description

The year is $year. The season is $season. The Hero Wars are coming—and the Red Cow clan must survive.

[[Continue->1618 Opening]]

::1618 Opening
The wind carries whispers from the east. The Telmori have been quiet for a season—but the elders remember when they wiped out the Maboder tribe. The Lunar Empire rules through their puppet prince, and the rebellion stirs in the hills.

You stand at the gates of Red Cow Fort, looking out at the lands your ancestors fought for.

What do you do?

* [[Join the moot (political)->Moot 1618]]
* [[Patrol the borders (action)->Border Patrol]]
* [[Visit the temple (story)->Temple Visit]]

::Moot 1618
<<set _roll = (call: "factionRoll", "Oratory", 15)>>
The moot gathers at the fort—the chieftain's council, debating the response to Lunar tribute demands. Broddi Strong-Kin speaks for peace. Darna Longcoat shouts for war.

<<if _roll.result is "great">>
You sway the moot with your words. ((Your contribution helps the Conquering Storm faction gain influence.))
<<call "updateFaction", "conqueringStorm", 2>>
<<call "advanceArc", "thorvald", 1>>
<<elseif _roll.result is "success">>
You speak well, and the moot considers your words.
<<call "updateFaction", "conqueringStorm", 1>>
<<else>>
Your words fall flat—the council is divided, and nothing is resolved.
<</if>>

[[Continue->1618-2]]

::Border Patrol
<<set _roll = (call: "factionRoll", "Awareness", 13)>>
You ride the borders of the clan lands, watching for Telmori signs.

<<if _roll.result is "great">>
You spot signs of a Telmori scouting party—three wolves, moving east. You report to the thanes.
<<call "updateFaction", "wolfskinners", 2>>
<<call "advanceArc", "rok", 1>>
<<elseif _roll.result is "success">>
You see nothing unusual—but the ride is peaceful.
<<call "updateFaction", "wolfskinners", 1>>
<<else>>
You nearly ride into a Telmori patrol—they let you go, for now. A warning.
<</if>>

[[Continue->1618-2]]

::Temple Visit
<<set _roll = (call: "factionRoll", "Faith", 15)>>
You visit the temple of your cult—Ernalda's shrine for healing, Orlanth's hall for war.

<<if _roll.result is "great">>
The priest blesses you. You feel the favor of the gods.
<<call "updateFaction", "eyeOfHurricane", 2>>
<<call "advanceArc", "erlana", 1>>
<<elseif _roll.result is "success">>
The temple is peaceful. You rest.
<<call "updateFaction", "eyeOfHurricane", 1>>
<<else>>
The temple is emptying—more follow the Lunar Way each season.
<</if>>

[[Continue->1618-2]]

::1618-2
The first crisis comes three days later.

A runner from the eastern steads: "Children taken. Wolves in the night."

The Telmori have broken the peace. The Missing has begun.

What do you do?

* [[Pursue the kidnappers (combat)->Chase Scene]]
* [[Tend the wounded (healing)->Healing Scene]]
* [[Investigate the trail (scouting)->Trail Scene]]

::Chase Scene
<<set _roll = (call: "roll")>>
You ride after the Telmori who took the children.

Char rolled: $_roll.charDie vs Resist $_roll.resistDie
Result: $_roll.result

<<if $_roll.result is "victory" or $_roll.result is "critical">>
You catch the Telmori raiders. A bloody fight—but the children are rescued.
<<call "updateFaction", "wolfskinners", 2>>
<<call "advanceArc", "rok", 1>>
<<elseif $_roll.result is "mixed">>
You drive them off, but the children are gone—taken to Staland.
<<call "updateFaction", "wolfskinners", 1>>
<<else>>
The Telmori are too fast. You return empty-handed.
<</if>>

[[Continue->1618 End]]

::Healing Scene
<<set _roll = (call: "factionRoll", "Healing", 17)>>
The wounded are brought to you—the stead burned, three dead, four taken.

<<if _roll.result is "great">>
Your healing saves lives. The survivors will remember.
<<call "updateFaction", "eyeOfHurricane", 2>>
<<call "advanceArc", "erlana", 1>>
<<elseif _roll.result is "success">>
You do what you can. Some will live.
<<call "updateFaction", "eyeOfHurricane", 1>>
<<else>>
Two die despite your efforts. The clan mourns.
<</if>>

[[Continue->1618 End]]

::Trail Scene
<<set _roll = (call: "factionRoll", "Tracking", 15)>>
You read the signs where the Telmori passed—blood, tracks, broken branches.

<<if _roll.result is "great">>
You learn where they're hiding. You can bring war.
<<call "updateFaction", "freeSartar", 2>>
<<call "advanceArc", "asvith", 1>>
<<elseif _roll.result is "success">>
The trail leads east—but fades at Staland.
<<call "updateFaction", "freeSartar", 1>>
<<else>>
The signs confuse you. The Telmori moved cleverly.
<</if>>

[[Continue->1618 End]]

::1618 End
<<set $year = 1619>>
<<set $season = "Sea Season">>
<<call "updateResources", "wealth", -1>>
<<call "updateResources", "warriors", -1>>
The year ends. The Missing is over—the children are rescued, or lost to the werewolves. The Red Cow survives—but the Telmori have tasted blood again.

<<if $clanResources.wealth <= 5>>
Despite your efforts, the clan's wealth has diminished. The winter will be hard.
<</if>>

The war is coming. You can feel it in the wind.

[[Book Two]->Season Transition]

::Season Transition
<<remember $year>>
<<remember $season>>
<<set _ending = (call: "checkEnding")>>

You have completed Year $year.

<<if $endingType == "freedom">>
The flame of rebellion burns bright. Your actions have shaped the clan's path toward liberation.
<<elseif $endingType == "collaboration">>
The Lunar Way spreads through the clan. Survival comes at a cost.
<<elseif $endingType == "exile">>
The clan crumbles. Only scattered survivors remain to carry on.
<<else>>
Your path remains unwritten. The future hangs in balance.
<</if>>

<<if $year >= 1625>>
Your current status:
- Free Sartar: $factionStanding.freeSartar
- Wolfskinners: $factionStanding.wolfskinners
- Moon Winds: $factionStanding.moonWinds
- Wealth: $clanResources.wealth

Ending: $endingType
<<else>>
What memories will carry you into $year+1?
<</if>>

[[End Demo]]

::Ending Check
<<set _ending = (call: "checkEnding")>>

<<if _ending == "freedom">>
<<set $gameLog += (array: "The Red Cow clan has won freedom!")>>
<<elseif _ending == "collaboration">>
<<set $gameLog += (array: "The clan survives under Lunar rule.")>>
<<elseif _ending == "exile">>
<<set $gameLog += (array: "The clan has fallen. Exile awaits.")>>
<<else>>
<<set $gameLog += (array: "The future remains unwritten.")>>
<</if>>